++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_system">
	A <b>class_system</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> 
	that defines classifications of product or activity data.
</ext_description>


<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_mim  Function: class_assignment_is_valid
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_assignment_is_valid">
The <b>class_assignment_is_valid</b> function evaluates whether an instance of <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/> is valid.
<p>If it assigns a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_system"/>, the role shall be 'class system membership', and, in its items attribute, only instances of types listed in <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_system_item"/> shall be found.</p>
<p>If it assigns a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.characterized_class"/>, its classification role shall be 'definitional', 'non-definitional' or empty, and, in its items attribute, only instances of types listed in <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.classified_item"/> shall be found.</p>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_assignment_is_valid.aia">
the instance of <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/>, the validity of which is assessed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_mim  Rule: restrict_classification_assignments
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.restrict_classification_assignments">
The <b>restrict_classification_assignments</b> rule ensures that instances of <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/> that assign a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.characterized_class"/> or a <express_ref linkend="classification_with_attributes:mim:Classification_with_attributes_mim.class_system"/> are valid.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.restrict_classification_assignments.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment"/> whose assignment is not valid.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_with_attributes_mim  Rule: restrict_group_relationship_for_classification_hierarchy
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.restrict_group_relationship_for_classification_hierarchy">
The <b>restrict_group_relationship_for_classification_hierarchy</b> rule ensures the existance of instances of <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/> for the relating and the related part of the classification hierarchy.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Classification_with_attributes_mim.restrict_group_relationship_for_classification_hierarchy.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group_relationship"/> whose relating or related part are not related to a <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/> instance.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
